      "description": "5 cm of the terminal ileum was harvested from TRPV1hM3Dq and littermate control hM3Dqfl/fl mice 24 hours after one dose of 0.1 mg/kg CNO via intraperitoneal injection. Tissues were fixed in 10% neutral-buffered formalin (VWR) for 24 hours at 4 ºC before being transferred to 70% ethanol at 4 ºC. Samples were then embedded in paraffin blocks and sectioned at 5um-thickness for spatial transcriptomics.\n\nXenium probes were hybridized in situ to target RNA molecules. Each probe contained a unique barcode sequence to enable transcript identification during sequencing-free imaging on the Xenium Analyzer. Xenium analyzer was used to image target RNA positions and cell boundaries. Proprietary software was used to decode and return transcript positions as outputs from the Xenium machine, along with raw images of cell nucleus and boundary stainings.\n\nXenium slides were processed using the following 10x Genomics user guides: CG000578 (preparation), CG000580 (deparaffinization), CG000749 (hybridization, amplification, staining), and CG000584 (instrument run).",
